***Given an array prices[] representing stock prices, find the maximum total profit that can be earned by buying and selling the stock any number of times***
***Note: We can only sell a stock which we have bought earlier and we cannot hold multiple stocks on any day***
By Accumulating Profit:
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
code:
from typing import List


class Solution:
    def maximumProfit(self, prices) -> int:
        # result intialize as 0
        res = 0
        # initialize n as the length of the price  arrat
        n = len(prices)
        # if the prices of the price index is les then price index - 1
        for i in range (1,n):
            if prices[i] > prices[i-1]:
                # result will be the sum of  the profit at everry iteration andd iff there is no profit then nothing will be added
                res += prices[i] - prices[i - 1]
            
        return res 
        
if __name__ == "__main__":
    prices = [100,180,234,40,535,695]
    ob = Solution()
    ob.maximumProfit(prices)
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Time Complexity: O(n)
Auxiliary Space: O(1)
